            <p><small>From Wikipedia, the free encyclopedia </small></p> <br /><br />

            <p><strong>Artichoke dip</strong> is a <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Dipping_sauce">dip</a> that uses <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Artichoke">artichoke</a>as a primary ingredient.Some versions are served chunky, while others are puréed and have a smooth texture. It may be served as an <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hors_d%27oeuvre">hors d'oeuvre</a> along with crackers or chips for dipping. Commercially prepared artichoke dips are produced for consumer purchase. It has been described as "one of the most popular <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Hors_d%27oeuvre">appetizer</a> menu items of all time".</p>

